  "prompt": "How many professional photographers are there in Canada?",
  "response": "Finding an exact number of professional photographers in Canada is tricky because there's no single, definitive registry. However, we can look at available data to get an estimated range.\n\n*   **Self-Identification:** Many photographers work as freelancers or under contract and may not be formally registered anywhere.\n\n*   **Industry Associations:** Associations like the Professional Photographers of Canada (PPOC) have members, but membership is voluntary.\n\n*   **Labour Force Surveys:** Statistics Canada collects data on occupations, but photography might be categorized under broader categories.\n\nGiven these challenges, some reports estimated around **4,000-5,000** professional photographers in Canada in 2024. This number fluctuates.\n",
